# Phase 5 — UX Bugs & Dead UI

Customer-facing fixes. One PR.

## Task 5.1 — Hide settings password change UI

**Files:**
- `src/app/(app)/settings/page.tsx`
- `src/components/settings/account-section.tsx`

**Why:** `(app)/settings/page.tsx:41` passes `onUpdatePassword={() => {}}`. Users will type their current password, type a new one, click "Update Password," see no error, and walk away thinking it worked. Their old password still works. This is a credential-handling silent failure — the worst kind of bug to ship.

**Fix (minimum viable):** replace the entire password section in `account-section.tsx` with a "Coming soon" placeholder, OR delete the password sub-section entirely until it's wired. Same for the email-change UI (it's also a no-op).

```tsx
