```

Then at lines 44 and 65, drop the `as JobStage` from `STAGE_UI_TO_PRISMA[data.stage as JobStage]` — it becomes `STAGE_UI_TO_PRISMA[data.stage]`. The Prisma stage type is still pulled from `@prisma/client` so keep `as PrismaJobStage` only if `STAGE_UI_TO_PRISMA`'s return type isn't already `PrismaJobStage`. Check the constant definition in `src/constants/job-stages.ts` first; if it returns `PrismaJobStage`, drop that cast too.

**`src/services/profile.ts:94`** — remove `as Record<string, string>` cast on `professionalLinks`. Zod now guarantees the shape, but the type stored in `Profile` is `Json` (Prisma) which Prisma maps to `unknown` on read. You'll still need *one* cast to `Record<string, string> | undefined` here because Prisma has no way to know the JSON shape — but it's narrowing-after-validation, not blind coercion. Add a one-line comment explaining why the cast is safe (zod validated on write).

## Task 2.5 — Update tests

**Files:**
- `src/tests/api/jobs-id.test.ts`
- `src/tests/api/profile.test.ts`

Add test cases for the validation path. Pattern:
