```

**Replacement:** Supabase auth errors include a `code` field on the error object (`AuthError` from `@supabase/supabase-js`). Check that instead. If the code is unstable too, fall back to checking `error.status === 422` (the HTTP status Supabase returns for duplicate signup).

```ts
if (error.status === 422 || error.code === "user_already_exists") {
  throw new ApiError(409, "Email is already registered. Please log in instead.");
